          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(center)">Finished</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                                        <date>9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Sivan (May)
                                        1849</date>.</p>
                              <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir: I immediately dispatched the desired
                                        book to<lb/> you, through the post. Since the post office
                                        accepted it bound, I<lb/> did not want to damage it by
                                        tearing off the covers. It cost<lb/> 25 cents without
                                        covers, and 20 cents, <del>bound</del> for the binding<lb/>
                                        Deduct 20%, leaves 36 cents. Add the cost of the
                                        Postage,<lb/> six cents, leaves 42 cents. Please write to me
                                        about it.<lb/> I give you 20% rebate, just as you do for me
                                        in your<lb/> publications. Nevertheless, if you agree to
                                        work for my book<lb/> business, I shall gladly offer you the
                                        highest rebate,<lb/> which is 30%. I still have not received
                                        the <date>May</date> issue of<lb/> the “Occident”. Please
                                        send me the <date>June</date> issue immedi<lb/>ately upon
                                        publication. I have just printed a catalogue<lb/> of my
                                        books and shall send you a copy with my next<lb/> number of
                                        the “Herald”. Do you want to advertise<lb/> it? And can you
                                        add it to the “Occident”?<lb/> If so, I urge your response
                                        by return mail and I shall<lb/> send you 300 copies by
                                        express.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I want to tell you that <persName>Mr.
                                                  Frank</persName> has begun<lb/> to print a prayer
                                        book with English translation, of the German<lb/> and Polish
                                        ritual. When this is done, perhaps you will want<lb/> to
                                        lower the price of yours before hand. I however, don't<lb/>
                                        want to advise you about this. Nor do I desire to cause<lb/>
                                        a loss to <persName>Mr. Frank.</persName> Nevertheless,
                                        since this matter is no<lb/> secret and will soon be
                                        publicly announced, I consider<lb/> it my duty to call your
                                        attention to it.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">With all respect,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Devotedly yours,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
